{"id":13830,"date":"2020-09-11T20:36:40","date_gmt":"2020-09-12T03:36:40","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/www.ronperrier.net\/?p=13830"},"modified":"2024-01-08T16:28:06","modified_gmt":"2024-01-09T00:28:06","slug":"kaslo-river-trail-2","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.ronperrier.net\/2020\/09\/11\/kaslo-river-trail-2\/","title":{"rendered":"KASLO RIVER TRAIL"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><em>This lovely urban trail network has two red-covered bridges to form a loop. Dioramas tell the history of the town. Artwork sculptures.<\/em><\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Rating:\u00a0\u2666\u2666\u2666\u25ca\u25ca<br \/>\n<\/strong><strong>Location:<\/strong> In the village of Kaslo<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Difficulty:<\/strong> A1 easy<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Elevation Gain:<\/strong> +55m<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Distance:<\/strong> 3.6 km<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Time:<\/strong> 90 minutes<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Season:<\/strong> April through November. Snowshoe in winter.<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Access:<\/strong> Excellent pavement 2WD low clearance<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Map:<\/strong> 82F\/15 Kaslo<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Drive.<\/strong> This trail loop has several access points. From downtown Kaslo, walk to the end of 5th Street that leads to the Unity Bridge<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Trail:<\/strong> Hike up the 1.3km north trail that hugs the river. It is an easy wide, wheel-chair accessible trail for 650m. It eventually branches into upper and lower trails. The lower trail follows along the river. The upper trail ends at the Upper Trailblazers Bridge.<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">After the bridge take the 1.9 km single trail south trail that leads to a viewpoint and also connects to the Kaslo airport and existing trails at the True Blue Recreation Area. Finally, loop back to the Unity Bridge that connects to 5<sup>th<\/sup> Street.<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">The highlight of the trail is the 7 comical wood sculptures among the boulders.<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">The trail follows a historic wood stave pipeline from the old dam site that produced power for Kaslo from 1897-1960. Interpretive maps and signs on the trail along with strategically placed benches allow walkers to enjoy magnificent views while contemplating the history of the area.<\/span><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>References:<\/strong><\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><a href=\"https:\/\/westkootenayhiking.ca\/kaslo-river\/\">https:\/\/westkootenayhiking.ca\/kaslo-river\/<\/a><\/span><\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>This lovely urban trail network has two red-covered bridges to form a loop. Dioramas tell the history of the town. Artwork sculptures. Rating:\u00a0\u2666\u2666\u2666\u25ca\u25ca Location: In the village of Kaslo Difficulty: A1 easy Elevation Gain: +55m Distance: 3.6 km Time: 90 &hellip; <a href=\"https:\/\/www.ronperrier.net\/2020\/09\/11\/kaslo-river-trail-2\/\">Continue reading <span class=\"meta-nav\">&rarr;<\/span><\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","sticky":fals